{
  "texts": [
    "(6.7)Now we claim that (6.2) and (6.5)/(6.6) are equivalent over standard frames.",
    "We already have the implication from (6.2) to (6.5), since (6.5) is equivalent to (6.3), which is simply an instantiation of (6.2).",
    "The implication from (6.5) to (6.2) relies on the following two key points:(A) If α:= ∀v(Qv ↔ ∀v ′ ⊑ v ∃v ′′ ⊑ v ′ Qv ′′)∧x ⊑ x 0 ∧∀y(xR i y → Qy) from (6.2) is satisfied in F with a variable assignment ν such that ν(x) = x, then ν(Q) is a regular open set that includes R i (x).",
    "Thus, ν(Q) is a superset of our int(cl(R i (x))) from (6.1), which we noted above is the minimal regular open set that includes R i (x).",
    "(B) Thanks to its positive syntactic form, β:= ∀z(xR 2 i z → Qz) from (6.2) is semantically upward monotone in Q: for any assignments ν and ν ′ that agree on x, if β is satisfied by F with ν ′, and ν ′ (Q) ⊆ ν(Q), then β is satisfied by F with ν.Let γ be the formula that comes after ∀x ⊑ x 0 in (6.5), and suppose γ is satisfied in F with some assignment ν."
  ]
